Perl bindings for the Elluminate Live Standard Bridge v2 API.

** DEVELOPER RELEASE - UNDER CONSTRUCTION **

Elluminate Live! (c) is software for virtual online classrooms. It is suitable
for meetings, demonstrations web conferences, seminars and IT deployment,
training and support.

Elive-StandardV2 is a set of Perl bindings and entity definitions for the
Elluminate Standard Bridge V2 SOAP services. 

This is a newer lightweight alternative to Elive which binds to the
Command Toolkit default SOAP services.

INSTALLATION
============
To install this module, run the following commands:

	perl Makefile.PL
	make
	make test
	make install

SERVER CONFIGURATION
====================

Elluminate Live Manager
-----------------------
Please ensure that your the standard bridge (v2) is enabled. To do this,
login to http://your_server.com/elmcontrol with an appropriate administrator
account.

Edit/create the appropriate server instance and tick 'Elluminate Standard
Bridge v2 ...' in the 'Bridge Selection' section.

You will then be asked to enter the SDK username and password. 

SUPPORT AND DOCUMENTATION
=========================
After installing, you can find documentation for this module with the
perldoc command.

    perldoc Elive::StandardV2

You can also look for information at:

    RT, CPAN's request tracker
        http://rt.cpan.org/NoAuth/Bugs.html?Dist=Elive-StandardV2

    AnnoCPAN, Annotated CPAN documentation
        http://annocpan.org/dist/Elive-StandardV2

    CPAN Ratings
        http://cpanratings.perl.org/d/Elive-StandardV2

    Search CPAN
        http://search.cpan.org/dist/Elive-StandardV2/


